Date:  0/0/1908
Source:  NZ Geol. Survey Bulletin
Author:
Vol / Page:  No. 5 (N.S.)/37
Edition:
Quote:  The basement rock is known to alluvial miners as 'reef bottom'; ... The 'reef bottom' may be slate and sandstone, as in Victoria; mica-schist, as in Otago; or granite, as in some parts of New South Wales and Queensland. <i>Ibid.</i> 42  Towards the dip it passes off the schist or `reef' bottom on to the lignite series.
Notes:  (Park: Cromwell)
